My family is more important to me than getting "there" a few minutes
earlier.  At 60 mph, with no stops, you get 60 miles in, well, an hour
(duh).  At 85 miles per hour, you get there in 42 minutes, a savings of
18 minutes.  Theorhetically, on a trip of 1000 miles (at 60 mph) you'd get
there in 16.5 hours.  At 85 you'd get there in 11.7 hours. You've saved
roughly 5 hours travel time, [...]

