I tend to plan my long trips using map software (M$ Streets and Trips) set
at 50mph. Then when I drive 55 - 65 I'm pleasantly surprised when I get
there "ahead of schedule".

10 extra mph moves you 240 miles closer to your destination in a 24 hour
period (seems the average distance to any campouts I attend regularly is
about 1400 - 1500 miles from my house <grin>).

